<% layout('/layouts/boilerplate') %>
<div class="card" style="width: 18rem">
    <div class="card-header">
        <h3 class="card-title text-center">Idiom</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-text"><%= card.english%></p>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-text"><%= card.spanish%></p>
    </div>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <li class="list-group-item"><%= card.hintOne%></li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><%= card.hintTwo%></li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Card by: <%= card.author.username%></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="card-body">
        <a href="/cards" class="btn btn-success btn-outline-dark">All Cards</a>
        <% if(currentUser && card.author.equals(currentUser._id)) { %>
        <a href="/cards/<%=card._id%>/edit" class="btn btn-outline-dark"
            >Edit</a
        >
        <form
            class="d-inline"
            action="/cards/<%=card._id%>?_method=DELETE"
            method="POST"
        >
            <button class="btn btn-danger btn-outline-dark">Delete</button>
        </form>
    </div>
    <% } %>
</div>
<!-- CAN ONLY DO GET OR POST -->
<!-- to display edit/delete to user that created the card we need two pieces of info: the card.author, which is supposed to be a userID; and also the currentUser, which will also contain an ID. We want to see if these match.

    The easisest way to do that is to do a card-author .equals() the currentUser._id, which will look like this: card.author.equals(currentUser._id). However this alone will break our app especially if nobody is signed in.

    SO TO FIX THIS we add currentUser && ..., which is saying if CURRENTUSER exists - meaning currentUser is activated, which will only happen after a user passes Authentication and logs-in. So the whole IF statement saying if currentUser exists AND (&&) card.author EQUALS currentUser_.id THEN display the BUTTONS that we want displayed (edit/delete)-->
